               <msContents>
                  <summary>Declaration on oath from Panopolis (modern name: Akhmim), Egypt, written on papyrus. Lists small holdings in various numbered plots in the Panopolite Nome. Types of land include sown land and dry land. Part of the archive of Ammon, the well-known scholastikos, or lawyer</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 11.5 x 12.8 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">12 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 1.5 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 181 was formerly P.Duk.inv. G 181</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
